name: North Gwinnett High School
directions: Go down the 400 hall past the front desk and they should be straight ahead

name: Obi
directions: At the entrance
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer.

name: KPMG
directions: Behind the ground floor coffee bar to the left of the reception desk
comment: The toilet is accessible from the building reception area (you don’t need to swipe through the employee card gates to get to it). The receptionists are usually very nice so you could maybe ask for directions if lost, but I’m not sure. I guess try to act like you should be there!

name: Earl’s Kitchen and Bar
directions: At back of bar and back of dining room
comment: Six single stall bathrooms. Three in dining room and three in bar area. All single stall, two female, two male, and two “family” with changing table. Use any restroom you prefer to use.

name: Bohemian Lane
comment: Es una cafetería + pastelería. No sé si hay que consumir algo para poder usar los baños

name: McDonald Road Library
directions: At the far right on the ground floor. Key to be collected from behind Librarian’s desk on the back wall on the ground floor.

name: Ofek Shalom Cooperative
directions: Three bathrooms in this cooperative house.
comment: House is a safe space for all that need it.

name: Jacob's Pickles
directions: Just past bar on right, plain door
comment: Restaurant, single room unisex, unmarked. Toilet and sink.

name: Heartland Humane Society
comment: Just ask at the front desk. Anyone is welcome to use the restroom during open hours: Tues/Wed/Fri 12pm-6pm, Sat/Sun 12pm-5pm

name: Bad Hunter
directions: Through the back door, all three bathrooms are single stall
comment: Do not have to make a purchase.

name: The Food Co-op Shop
comment: Change table available but needs to be requested as it is kept in store room to ensure wheelchair access.

name: Destihl Brewery
comment: The restrooms are gendered but the ladies is single stalled with sinks inside the stalls. No info on the mens.

name: Big Y
directions: Right by the entrance closest to the Dollar Tree, there are individual gendered bathrooms. I know the women's room has a changing table and believe the men's room does as well.
comment: I've never been bothered about using this bathroom, and there are no signs saying for paying customers only. Might be best to at least act like you plan to shop after peeing tho.

name: Zazzle Salon
directions: Accessible in the main room via the front entrance.
comment: It's a hair salon so it may be weird to just go in for the bathroom, but the owner has an open door policy & is very kind.

name: Coasters Coffee Co.
directions: Towards the back room by the chips.
comment: The coffee shop is really chill. They have an FtM employee.

name: Kroger
directions: Unmarked door to the left of the other bathrooms near the Starbucks. Has a vacancy/occupied sign on lock.
comment: Often used by employees, so sometimes a bit of a wait

name: Main Event Entertainment
directions: Restrooms are located to the left of the counter. The family restroom is in between the two gendered

name: Also Hana Sushi Grill
directions: Restrooms are located right after you walk in, behind the little curtain and to your right. It is a private restroom

name: Park Cafe
directions: Located in back right of restaurant

name: Frozen Monkey
directions: In the back of the shop, you have to walk down a long windy hallway to get to it

name: Highsmith Student Union
directions: On the second floor. On your left when facing the bridge. Right next to gendered bathrooms.
comment: Brand new, just added!

name: Boston University Fenway  Classroom Building
directions: Gender neutral single stalls on every floor
comment: Need to be a student or visitor of the College.

name: Common Ground Food Co-op
directions: Just past the registers, go left down the hallway, past the water fountain.
comment: The staf is overall very trans supportive and there are multiple trans people on staff, it's a safe space.

name: Boston Convention and Exhibition Center
directions: First Floor Southeast lobby.
comment: Great for if you're going to a Con there.

name: Cegep de carleton
directions: Au 2eme etage

name: Boston Ex
directions: First floor in the South East Lobby
comment: Great for if you are attending an event there or Con.

name: Lowes
comment: Family bathroom

name: Caesars head visitor center
directions: In back right hallway in visitor center.  Open 10am to 5pm 365 days a year.  No charge to enter park

name: Caesars head visitor center
directions: Inside the visitor center in back hallway in vending area.  No charge to enter park.  Open 10am-5pm. 365 days a year

name: Ohio Union
directions: Third floor on the south side of the Union, between to the two gendered restrooms

name: Bareburger
directions: Straight back to the right.
comment: Should be a paying customer. Depends how the host is feeling

name: Pauline Haass Public Library
directions: The family bathroom in the Youth area of the library.

name: Old Nick's Pub
directions: To the right of the bar in the back.
comment: This is a pub, 21 an older only after 8pm.

name: Meridian Building
directions: Next to the Cafe Yumm!
comment: Ask for code at Cafe Yumm!

name: Starbucks Coffee
comment: Damn near anyone can use this bathroom

name: Raising Cane’s Chicken Fingers
directions: In the back of the restaurant, behind the brick wall.
comment: Two unisex bathrooms; the one on the right side has a changing table.

name: Philz
directions: Both bathrooms are gender neutral.
comment: Very queer-friendly place, bathrooms and otherwise!

name: Café Starbucks Coffee
directions: Bathroom door code: 1213
comment: Sometimes a barista will give you the code without purchase and some baristas won't.

name: Forest Lawn Bottle Depot
directions: To the right beside the sorters.  May need to ask for key.
comment: It’s a bottle depot so not the cleanest.

name: Taco Bell
comment: Two single-person(lockable), gender-neutral restrooms.

name: Kalamazoo Public Library
directions: Lower Level they changed men's and women's to two GNC rooms - stalls,urinals,changing table
comment: M-R 9am-9pm Friday 9-6 Saturday 9-5 Sunday 1-5

name: Waffle House
directions: walk in and go straight to the left, you'll find both bathrooms side by side

name: Waffle House
directions: walk in and go left, bathrooms are right next to each other

name: Barkley Annex Bathrooms
directions: South end of building

name: Jack In The Box
directions: Walk in the front door and take a right past the counter.

name: Back of Calios
directions: In the back entrance, to the left of the  food counter.
comment: You don't have to buy anything, or explain why you're there.

name: Target
directions: Family restroom just to left of front doors
comment: You can walk straight to bathroom

name: Bill's Music
directions: All the way in the back in the lessons area, on the left.
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer. Ask any staff member if you can't find it, they'll point you right to it.

name: Massage Envy Spa
comment: It’s a spa, so I assume you probably have to be a customer.

name: Beijing Capital Airport
directions: A bunch of single stall, accessible restrooms near E gates in airport.

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store
comment: Non-gendered “Family restroom”, single occupancy

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store
comment: Family bathroom single occupancy

name: Gibson's Bookstore
directions: 2 unisex, single stall bathrooms near the middle of the store, plus a third in the children's department with a changing table.

name: Universidad Sagrado Corazon
directions: Basement of of the library
comment: You need to be a student, prof or employee

name: St. John’s College
directions: First floor, McDowell Hall; up a flight of stairs. Elevator in the basement coffee shop for wheelchair accessibility
comment: An academic building but there will be no problem with anyone using the restrooms

name: Interdisciplinary Science & Technology Building IV
directions: Separate single stall room on each floor.
comment: Not sure about the changing table situation - might be one in the bathrooms on the public floors!

name: Eugene Family YMCA
comment: You have to have a membership or day pass. It’s an lgbtq friendly establishment however

name: BonChon Chicken
comment: Korean restaurant chain, probably have to be a customer

name: Shell
directions: One in each hallway on either side of the cash registers.
comment: You may want to buy something small, even just a bottle of water.

name: Creswell Hall
directions: First floor in the waiting room across from the community office. You may ask the 24-hour desk worker for directions as well.
comment: Open to the public. You do not have to be a resident of the hall.

name: Creswell Hall
directions: You can ask the desk assistant for directions to the bathroom if needed. It is next to the waiting area on the first floor you enter on.
comment: Public restroom.

name: Lou Lou’s
directions: At back end of restaurant.

name: Schoolcraft College
directions: Schoolcraft has unisex bathrooms for the purpose of trans individuals on campus. The buildings that have them are the Jeffress Center, Applied Science, Liberal Arts, and I believe the Forum. Maps near each entryway should point out unisex bathrooms

name: Layne's Chicken Fingers
directions: Immediately to the left when entering from the front; has a wooden frame and a sign with a joke about a chicken coop above.
comment: The entry to the little hall with the restrooms (men's to the left, women's to the right) is open, but each of the actual bathroom doors aren't visible from the rest of the restaurant.

name: Barbican Centre
directions: Currently converting all toilets into gender neutral, currently there is an accessible gender neutral toilet on the lowest floor of the Barbican centre by the cinema

name: Layne's Chicken Fingers
directions: Immediately to the left when entering from the front; has a wooden frame and a sign with a chicken coop joke above.
comment: The entry to the little hall is sort of wide open (turn left for men's, right for women's) but each of the actual bathroom doors aren't visible from the rest of the restaurant.

name: Wal-Mart
directions: Back of the store, next to electronics, by customer service.

name: Tim Horton's
directions: Straight to the back of the store after you enter through the front, you should be able to to see it as soon as you walk in

name: McAlister Auditorium
directions: In short hallway to the right in the lobby.

name: Shakespear’s Globe
directions: First floor to the left and then you’ll see the signs.
comment: Gendered restrooms and a genderneutral single stall.

name: Wombat’s City Hostel
directions: Inside to the right.
comment: The stalls are not gendered, just sitting down or standing up signs.
